-- Higher tax bill hurts Ingersoll-Rand's profit
-- By Rohit T. K. in Bangalore
-- Wed Apr 23, 2014 07:22AM EDT
-- None



April 23 (Reuters) - Ingersoll-Rand Plc <IR.N>, maker of Trane airconditioners, reported a 10 percent decline in quarterly profit as its tax bill jumped.

The company's net profit fell to $79 million, or 28 cents per share, in the first quarter ended March 31 from $88 million, or 29 cents per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBwDyMqa] Provision for income tax rose to $24.5 million from $4.5 million in the year ago, the company said.